---
title: Herbed Portobello Mushroom Salad with Roasted Red Peppers, Parmesan & Garlic Butter Croutons
description: You ever go to an Italian-American red sauce joint and order a big chopped salad? The kind you just start craving on a random Wednesday night? Well, this salad tastes like that old-school favorite, starring meaty roasted portobellos and silky roasted red peppers. They’re served over a crisp salad of crunchy romaine, cool cukes, and juicy tomatoes. And you’ll recognize the dressing as that creamy Italian vinaigrette that’s zesty with the right touch of herbs. Finished with Parmesan and croutons, this substantial dinner-worthy salad is ready in 30 minutes to hit your table—with or without a red checkered tablecloth.
